description: Tara Mehta is the modern incarnation of Devi, a celestial warrior goddess who has sworn to protect the city of Sitapur. Now, however, Devi finds herself on the wrong side of the law she has sworn to uphold, as the police name her the prime suspect in a series of vicious murders. Making matters worse, monstrous Darinde soldiers of the dark god Bala are resurfacing in Sitapu, obeying the commands of a mysterious new leader. Devi finds herself torn between proving her own innocence, and countering this deadly new threat.

description: Daniel Defoe has woven a fantastic tale of the adventures of Robinson Crusoe, a young lad form the City of York in England who yearns for the life of the sea. His father wants Robinson to attend law school and get a good education, but Robinson decides otherwise. Follow Robinson as he survives pirates, shipwrecks and cannibals.

1. No Mercy for a Hero! (Superboy, Lana Lang, Ma and Pa Kent (both cameos) / written by Leo Dorfman)

An alien from Belgor named Ron-Avon gives Superboy an ultimatum: Challenge him in a best 2 of 3 contest or he turns the residents of Smallville into metal! Will Superboy win these contests? If he loses the Smallvillians will be turned to metal too! And will Superboy kill Ron if he does win? If Superboy doesn't kill him, then Ron's parents will get killed. What can Superboy do?

description: Spartan joins Stormwatch after the events of Wildstorm Rising. Spartan believes his teammates of the WildC.A.T.S have died in an exploding space craft and finds purpose in Stormwatch. The team is then gathered to confront Despot and his Warguard, who have recently been released from cryogenic stasis.

As his willpower grows, Hal Jordan continues to fight the forces of the Spectre. But is the world ready for him? And what exactly does Hal Jordan's return mean to the Guardian, Ganthet?

Plus, Green Arrow makes a startling discovery as a hero from the stars returns!
name: Yellow

description:
Angel lost the battle. Los Angeles was sent to hell. The story of what happened during that fateful first night concludes, in this super-sized, jaw-dropping issue. The answers you've been waiting for, the stories you wanted to see. Heroes will fall, new champions will rise, and you'll also see the long-awaited return of... right, like we're going to tell you here.

Brace yourself. Joss Whedon, Brian Lynch, and a host of the comics industry's most talented artists bring you more First Night!

Betta George is still kept by Gunn.

Wesley wakes up next to Fred and soon learns that it is an illusion and that he is to be the new liaison to the Senior Partners.

Kate Lockley returns and saves Conner from a group of demons and takes him back to her place where they talk for a short time, then she left, and Conner decided  to fight back ageist hell.
name: First Night, Part 2

description:
Overview

Continuing the startling rebirth of Hal Jordan with an issue guest-starring three of DC¹s most powerful teams: the Justice League of America (JLA), Justice Society of America (JSA) and Teen Titans. One of the deadliest villains in the DCU returns: Parallax! Things continue to twist and turn for John Stewart, Guy Gardner and Kilowog as they come face-to-face with their greatest enemy -- the man who destroyed the Green Lanterns. Meanwhile, Green Arrow struggles to find a way to stop Parallax as the JLA, the JSA and the Teen Titans join the fight!
name: Force of Will

description: Stormwatch reels from their confrontation against the Warguard. Spartan gives Stormwatch enough time to escape and rush back to Skywatch. They enact a plan to crash Skywatch into Death Valley with the Warguard on board and they do just that. Battalion and Timespan arrive from the past just in time to deal with the Warguard.

An 80 page Giant G-50 all reprint issue.

description:
Overview

In this shocking issue, learn the final fate of Kyle Rayner! And as Hal Jordan's rebirth explodes across the DCU, the Justice League of America (JLA) continues its epic battle against one of the oldest powers in the Universe. But are the heroes prepared for the return of Hal Jordan, Green Lantern?

Overview

Only after separating himself of the Spectre and Parallax, Hal Jordan return to his role of Earth's principle Green Lantern.

After a viciuos battle against Parallax, Jordan is ready to continue being the greatest Green Lantern ever.

description: Battalion is back to battle Despot and it is revealed how he survived "death" so many months ago. Battalion went into hiding and trained his powers to their utmost, preparing to face his father and the Warguard. Despot takes advantage of the battle by possessing the members of Stormwatch as well, combining them with the Warguard to defeat Battalion. He finds a way to sever Despot's ties and battles him head on, showing Despot his human side. In a moment of vulnerability, Henry Bendix arrives to shoot Despot in the head.
Stormwatch finally gathers together and defeats Despot utterly.
name: And In The End...

Following the tragic accident on Grok's homeworld, Zen goes into isolation -- only to find himself imprisoned for a crime he didn't commit!

description: Ethan and Ashleigh return to the Sanctuary Isle to find it the target of an attack by freebooters who see the island as easy prey now that the Raven and Heron Kingdoms no longer protect it. Will the dream of a free land for the Lesser Races end in blood and flames?

The distant land of Tigris seems almost utopian, a society that has embraced technology to solve all its ills. But is something sinister hiding beneath that veneer? Ethan and Ashleigh are about to find out, including learning the shocking truth about their friend Nadia!

The Underground's attempt at founding a free kingdom for the Lesser Races has been successful, but nothing is as simple as that. Told from the point of view of the Lesser Races, this issue delves into what it means to be a slave, as well as the courage it takes to throw off the chains of servitude and begin the long journey to freedom.
A member of Ethan's family dies.but whom? As the mighty kingdoms are pounded under the onslaught of the Tigris war machine, which Heron makes the ultimate sacrifice?

Ethan and Skink's quest to return home and prevent a planet-wide war is jeopardized by one of the savage storms that ravage the sea separating East and West. A race of undersea creatures could be the companions' only hope or a danger even greater than that of nature's unleashed fury.

Desperately trying to make their way home, Ethan and his sidekick Skink are on the run in Eastern lands, barely managing to stay one step ahead of Bron's search parties. When their trail is picked up by a brutal bounty hunter from the Lesser Races, even the power of Ethan's sigil might not be enough to save him.

Even Ethan's power might not be enough to save him as he attempts to settle the war between the Ravens and the Herons in a manner no one expects. But even if Ethan manages to put an end to the centuries-old conflict, his hated enemy Bron still waits to take his revenge. Two years worth of stories come to a head as Scion celebrates its second anniversary.

Regular series penciler Jim Cheung returns! A man claiming to be Bron, long presumed dead, returns to the Raven Kingdom. Is he really the missing monarch, or something else altogether? And even if he is who he says he is, will his brother Kort relinquish the throne so easily?

The epic war between the Ravens and Herons has been decided, but there's still one battle to be fought: Ethan vs. Bron! The two foes finally meet once again at the site of their first combat, the sands of the Tournament Arena. But this time the battle is to the death, and only one will walk away!

Imprisoned in Tigris, Ethan and Ashleigh are forced to undertake a desperate escape attempt. But even if they're successful, can they possibly return home in time to warn their kingdoms of what Tigris intends? Meanwhile, a peace summit between Bron and King Dane ends with a shocking turn!

Ethan and his family mourn the loss of one of their own as a royal funeral is held. Soon after the body is laid to rest, a stranger from distant lands arrives at the Heron castle, offering his services as war adviser and taking particular interest in Ethan's sigil. As thoughts turn to revenge against the East, Ethan is forced to make a decision that could mean turning his back on his family forever.

Bron takes center stage in an issue built around the Eastern prince's dogged pursuit of a Lesser Races slave who has escaped from the Raven Keep. Bron's crusade brings him face to face with Ashleigh, the mysterious benefactor of the Underground, and their clash reveals stunning secrets about both of them.

Back in Eastern lands to exact his vengeance upon Bron, Ethan decides to seek out Ashleigh and the Underground movement. But he finds an unexpected obstacle standing in his way, Exeter, the bounty hunter Ethan believed dead. Even if Ethan manages to survive a rematch with Exeter, does the Heron prince have any chance of locating the Underground's sanctuary?

Ethan receives a less-than-hospitable welcome at the Underground's hidden sanctuary as he falls under suspicion for his royal heritage. Ethan's stay is short-lived, and he continues his journey northward, toward an encounter beyond his wildest imagining. The young prince is confronted by the spirit of his dead brother Artor, who imparts to Ethan secrets concerning not only his destiny, but the very nature of the sigil he bears. Plus, part one of a back-up story starring Exeter the Bounty Hunter, written by Ron Marz and drawn by Andrea DiVito!

While Ethan searches for Ashleigh, she's in the one place he'd never dream, or dare, to look: the Raven Keep. Ashleigh becomes embroiled in the court intrigues of the Raven Dynasty, not only bringing her face to face with the Raven king, but also leading to a confrontation with a mysterious warrior woman who has pledged to aid the Raven war effort.

A more powerful Bron makes his bid for the Raven throne. The only thing standing in his way ? his own father! Meanwhile, still intent on taking his revenge against Bron, Ethan clandestinely makes his way into the Eastern capital and attempts to steal into the very heart of the Raven Keep. But instead of finding his enemy, Ethan discovers an unexpected captive.

Ethan finally confronts the man against whom he's sworn a death oath ? Prince Bron, murderer of Ethan's brother. With Bron's sister Ashleigh bearing witness, the ensuing battle is fought in the very seat of Raven power and ends with a shocking climax that must be seen!

Ethan discovers that founding a kingdom may well be easier than maintaining one. As Ethan realizes he may not be the best choice to govern the freed Lesser Races simply because he's human, an assassin stalks him. Will the shadowy killer end not only Ethan's reign, but his life as well?

The mysterious Nadia of Tigris has been a staunch ally for Ethan and the Underground's cause. But now she reveals her true purpose and true loyalty, forcing Ethan to make a choice that could decide the fate of his fledgling kingdom.

1. The best criminal brains of all time, the most ruthless killers and thieves ever to plague mankind, brought back from the past into the modern world by a master of evil, and all bent on the annihilation of Captain America in "Masters of Evil"
  2. The Human Torch and Toro meet "The Swanky Swindlers" when the soldier and the girl who dreamed of getting married one day are beset by the gangster that was dead set on seeing they never did.
  3. Water leaves no tracks, neither does electricity! That's how Death head Scott figured when he planned the perfect crime! Speed was his trump card, but he forgot one man who is faster than light, faster even than electricity, The Whizzer in "The Discs of Death"
name: Masters Of Evil

description: Romance is in the air - finally - for Ethan and Ashleigh. Since giving in to their attraction the pair have hardly had a chance to catch their breath, much less make time to explore their newfound love. But now that they actually have a chance to be together, will they discover they're not meant for each other after all? Meanwhile, a threat literally looms on the horizon.
The hunt for King Dane begins! Prince Ethan and his siblings Kai and Ylena search for their missing father, but with all of Avalon to search, can they find him before it's too late?

A special stand-alone, all double-page spread issue! Told in the tradition of Hal Foster's legendary Prince Valiant Sunday pages, this issue's amazingly detailed double-page spreads will bring to breathtaking life the story of Prince Ethan and the techno-medieval world of Avalon! If you've ever wanted to check out SCION, or if you're just a lover of great art, this is the issue for you!

Key Issue! Instead of fighting each other, can the Heron and Raven kingdoms fight side- by-side? They better...because the robotic empire of Tigris is on the attack! With the new creative team of Ian Edginton (Batman/Aliens II) and Luke Ross kicking off a new story arc, now is the perfect time to join the SCION saga!

World War! The full-scale Tigris invasion begins as thousands of robotic shock troops lay siege to the already bombarded Raven and Heron capitals! Meanwhile, Ethan and Ashleigh have problems of their own as a Tigris occupation force seeks to transform Tournament Isle into a command center!

1. In "The China Wall Mystery" Captain America battles on the Great China Wall, symbol of an unconquerable people! But what strange figure haunts its ancient passages? What unanswered enigma stalks the olden tunnels and gives aid to captain America as he crushes a cunning Jap plot?
  2. "Death Cargo" Messenger Service -- Torch and Toro: You are cordially invited to witness a series of murders scheduled to occur at the stroke of midnight on the 8th day of...
  3. A newly won B-32 base, only a few hundred miles from the nip homeland, attacked under mysterious and puzzling circumstances! And once again, that Jap busting hero, Captain johnson locks with a desperate enemy in "Air Base"
name: The China Wall Mystery

description:
1. Murder -- Done over crumpled scraps of paper covered with mysterious scrawls! Captain America and Bucky battle "Knucks" Connors and his killer mob to unlock the enigma of "The Tick-Tack-Toe Murder!"
  2. NYLON! An important factor in winning the war! Nylon for glider tow-lines, parachutes, and countless other life-saving devices! Nylon desperately needed by our brave troops! That's why thinking patriotic Americans stood stunned with horror as they watched precious quantities of essential material being diverted into black market hosiery! Then the Human Torch and Toro took a hand and matched their wits against the diabolical and ruthless cunning of the "Black Marketeers of Death".
  3. A fierce battle rages in the skies, two planes lock in deadly combat. Two Pilots -- and one must die! For when Jap Buster Johnson tangles with Japan's deadliest ace, the law of the jungle prevails, kill or be killed in "Kito, Japanese Fighter Pilot"
name: The Tick-Tack-Toe Murder!

description:
1. The name on her bow is Tranquility, but the crew on her deck spells trouble! And what begins as just another week-end of yachting, runs into a tidal wave of turbulence with Captain America and Bucky hard put to keep their grip on the helm and their feet firmly planted on dangerous decks when "Crime Takes A Cruise!"
  2. An important military figure vanishes into thin air! and with him goes the most closely guarded secret in the world! Who is behind this amazing kidnapping? Who are his captors? Even the Torch and his pal, Toro didn't know the answer, until they recieved "A Message From The Dead!"
  3. Rocky Scardulla, the man who is as crooked as a bent pretzel, goes straight. That's Rocky's story and a pretty good one too, until The Destroyer investigates to learn the truth in "Agency Of Death"
  4. The Sub-Mariner investigates murder on a movie set in "Horror Island"
name: Crime Takes A Cruise!

description: The new recruits in Stormwatch are in Iraq, on a mission that should be easy, but give them valuable experience. Unfortunately, they are attacked by a terrorist group called Heaven's Fist, a group of super-powered killers. The amateur Stormwatch team proves to be no match for Heaven's Fist and the veteran members are called in to handle the situation.

IDW Publishing and Gold Eagle Books continue the all-new comic adventures of Don Pendleton's Mack Bolan, the Executioner! The original one-man army continues his battle against the Border Steel Cartel. Bolan and a pair of ATF agents meet to discuss the Cartel when violence explodes on the streets of Brownsville. Can Bolan keep the bloodshed from claiming innocent lives? Writer Doug Wojtowicz and artist S.L. Gallant deploy once more, with Rebecca A. Wrigley providing literally blazing cover fire.
name: The Devil's Tools #2

description: Suburban Seattle, the mid-1970s. A strange plague has descended upon the area's teenagers, transmitted by sexual contact, that manifests in any number of ways - from the hideously grotesque to the subtle and concealable. What unfolds isn't the expected battle to fight the plague, or bring heightened awareness to it, or even to treat it. Instead, Black Hole paints a fascinating and eerie portrait of the nature of high school alienation itself - the savagery, the cruelty, the relentless anxiety and ennui, the longing for escape. As hypnotically beautiful as it is horrifying, Black Hole deftly explores a specific American cultural moment in flux and the kids who are caught in it.

We've given you thousands of stories. You've picked the best! Here come the 100 Greatest Marvels Of All Time! Heads up, True Believers! In honor of our fantastic 40th Anniversary, we're counting down the 100 best Marvel Comics ever -- and we're reprinting the Top 25 based on your votes! Over 50,000 ballots were sent in to The House, each one hand-counted and tabulated with tenacity by our very own boisterous Bullpen! The results were sealed and guarded by Lockjaw -- until now! What are the top titles that we've ever printed? The voting spanned every era of Marvel majesty -- but we're not saying who came out the winners just yet, gang! The only way to find out is to pick up these handsome reprint collections as we work our way down to what you, the mighty Marvel masses, have deemed the #1, hands-down champion -- the Greatest Marvel Comic Of All Time!

Format: Color; Anthology; 112 Pages
